bib_record.title: Multiple Moments of 154Sm, 176Yb, 232Th, and 238U from Proton Inelastic Scattering

free_txt: The data have been analyzed in the standard manner
using a deformed optical model potential to determine
the transition matrix elements. The calculations were
carried out using the coupled channels code ECIS of
J. Raynal. The best fit results for elastic
scattering indicate that inclusion of spin-orbit
interaction is necessary to describe the minima, most
noticeable for 176Yb. The procedure for fitting the
inelastic scattering data was based on grid-searchers,
including the 0+, 2+, and 4+ states, and deformation
parameters. In extracting cross sections, the peak
shapes were assumed to be identical for all states in
a particular spectrum. The peak areas were extracted
by an iterative procedure based on the shape of the
elastic peak with low energy tail varied to assure a
best fit for all states of interest.
